These are the girls who have completely changed my life in Kansas City ♥️ Moving to a new city as an adult is challenging in many ways, especially when it’s a place without a lot of fellow transplants. Aside from having Suzi (and Mr. Suzi), I spent many years feeling alone in KC. My life here felt very small at times because I lacked meaningful friendships. Over the last two years and even as recent as this summer, I’ve connected with these women in such impactful ways. They’ve welcomed me into their families and my life is so much fuller with them in it. Girlfriends make life so much better I want you to know it’s never too late to find your people.
Meet my alter ego: Rich B**** Housewife🍸🎀🖤 (IG won’t let me spell it out🙄)

Today was just an off day for me. Nothing in particular happened but I woke up sad and missing my mom more than usual. Mitch took me out for lunch but I didn’t like what I ordered and then I tried a new latte but didn’t like that either. Then I went to therapy and dealt with a lot of not so fun stuff. The holidays are always a struggle for me but surprisingly the beginning of each new year is a struggle too. It officially marks another year I won’t have my mom on this Earth with me. The last few days have also been weighing on me. I’m so thankful my husband was able to walk away from football relatively unscathed (aside from 2 spinal surgeries), but not every family can say the same.
